THE anti-stock theft community and two cops have successfully recovered 151 suspected stolen livestock in Matsieng in Free State. According to Warrant Officer Mmako Mophiring, the livestock is believed to be from KZN. He said on Sunday, 30 January at about 5pm, anti-stock theft community members received information about suspected stolen livestock at Matsieng mountain in Qwaqwa. “The team went to the mountain, where they found livestock. It was 117 sheep, eight cattle and 26 goats. It is suspected the livestock was stolen from KwaZulu-Natal and left there as a cool-off place,” Mophiring said. He said an inquiry has been opened and investigations were continuing.